  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who has shown remorse by partially repaying the embezzled funds. While embezzlement is a serious breach of fiduciary duty, the amount involved ($25,000) does not warrant a lengthy prison term. The disruption in the courtroom by a spectator is irrelevant to the legal merits of the case and does not influence the sentencing. Considering the goal of rehabilitation and the lack of a criminal record, a custodial sentence of 6 months is deemed appropriate to serve as a deterrent while allowing for reintegration.",
  "verdict": 6
}
